That is so lame. I don't know why Verant doesn't have work-arounds for that kind of thing. Let's look at it; why would you kill a fellow magician to get his thingy? Answer: one of the two of you is evil. Okay, so let's say you have a high elf magician NPC... a dark elf mage just offs him and takes the quest piece. A fellow high elf would walk up to him, say, &quot;Hey, magic dude, I need your thingy&quot; and the the magician would send him off on a microquest to prove himself worthy of getting the thingy (like a 24 hour camp of something where people with bad alignment can't go.) So, you kill him, regardless of alignment, you take a huge faction hit with Snooty Magicians of Felwithe or whatever.<br>
<br>
Dunno why Verant has you killing folks you shouldn't kill when they can get around it this way and make the game more fun in the process.<br>
